      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "Leo loved his black umbrella because it was strong and reliable.",
              "audioStart": 0.1,
              "audioEnd": 3.375
            },
            {
              "text": "One rainy Tuesday, he took the bus home after a long day at the office.",
              "audioStart": 4.237,
              "audioEnd": 8.175
            },
            {
              "text": "The rain fell hard against the windows, and the bus was very crowded.",
              "audioStart": 9.037,
              "audioEnd": 12.725
            },
            {
              "text": "When he arrived at his stop, he jumped off quickly without remembering his favorite item.",
              "audioStart": 13.588,
              "audioEnd": 17.875
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "He did not realize his loss until he walked into his apartment.",
              "audioStart": 18.738,
              "audioEnd": 21.975
            },
            {
              "text": "The umbrella was left behind on the seat, where it remained as the bus continued through the city.",
              "audioStart": 22.837,
              "audioEnd": 27.663
            },
            {
              "text": "A young woman named Sarah found it later that night.",
              "audioStart": 28.525,
              "audioEnd": 31.062
            },
            {
              "text": "If she had not taken it, the umbrella might have remained there until the bus company cleaned the vehicle.",
              "audioStart": 31.925,
              "audioEnd": 36.875
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "Sarah was an artist who traveled across the city to paint urban scenes.",
              "audioStart": 37.737,
              "audioEnd": 41.487
            },
            {
              "text": "She took the umbrella to the park, where it protected her from a sudden afternoon storm.",
              "audioStart": 42.35,
              "audioEnd": 46.75
            },
            {
              "text": "Later, she used it as a prop in a photograph for her new project.",
              "audioStart": 47.612,
              "audioEnd": 51.175
            },
            {
              "text": "The umbrella was taken on many adventures that Leo never could have imagined.",
              "audioStart": 52.038,
              "audioEnd": 55.95
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "Leo decided to contact the bus station the next morning.",
              "audioStart": 56.812,
              "audioEnd": 59.9
            },
            {
              "text": "He hoped that someone had found his property, but the worker told him that nothing had been reported.",
              "audioStart": 60.763,
              "audioEnd": 65.6
            },
            {
              "text": "Leo felt sad because he had owned that umbrella for many years.",
              "audioStart": 66.463,
              "audioEnd": 69.75
            },
            {
              "text": "He wondered where it was and who might be holding it now.",
              "audioStart": 70.612,
              "audioEnd": 73.213
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "Weeks passed, and Leo eventually bought a new umbrella.",
              "audioStart": 74.075,
              "audioEnd": 77.025
            },
            {
              "text": "However, he still remembered the old one every time it rained.",
              "audioStart": 77.888,
              "audioEnd": 81.175
            },
            {
              "text": "One day, he saw a beautiful picture in a local shop window.",
              "audioStart": 82.037,
              "audioEnd": 85.425
            },
            {
              "text": "It was a painting of a black umbrella standing in the middle of a colorful park.",
              "audioStart": 86.287,
              "audioEnd": 90.237
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "Leo recognized the umbrella immediately because of a small mark on the handle.",
              "audioStart": 91.1,
              "audioEnd": 95.125
            },
            {
              "text": "He entered the shop and asked the owner about the artwork.",
              "audioStart": 95.987,
              "audioEnd": 98.675
            },
            {
              "text": "The owner told him that a local artist had created the painting during a rainy season.",
              "audioStart": 99.537,
              "audioEnd": 103.825
            },
            {
              "text": "Leo felt happy that his lost thing was still part of a great story.",
              "audioStart": 104.688,
              "audioEnd": 108.15
            }
          ]
        }
